<HEADLINE>
<P>
STEPHEN CUSKEY; RESEARCH BIOLOGIST WORKED ON TOXIC WASTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Research microbiologist Stephen Cuskey, 36, who developed so-called suicide 
genes that self-destruct after making toxic wastes decompose. 
</P>
<P>
Cuskey worked at the Environmental Protection Agency Research Laboratory at 
Pensacola Beach, Fla. The laboratory specializes in the study of toxins and 
gene splicing and supervised the use of fertilizer to speed the growth of 
oil-eating bacteria to help clean up the Alaskan oil spill last year. In 
Pensacola on Thursday of a pancreatic infection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
