<HEADLINE>
<P>
YEAR-ROUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have been a year-round teacher for the Tehachapi Unified School District. Our 
district, faced with the exact population-explosion problem as Los Angeles, was 
forced to adopt the system. 
</P>
<P>
Our district attempted to pass a bond issue but the voters rejected it, forcing 
the year-round schedule. 
</P>
<P>
Many parents and community people howled about the "quality" education being 
diminished. Their solution, just like the middle-class parents in Los Angeles, 
was more money to prevent this. School districts adopting year-round schedules 
are saving facilities, improving education and providing a morale boost to 
teachers and students. Parents wanting a long summer vacation need to look at 
their "spoiled child" syndrome and support a system that saves tax dollars, 
time and enhances education. Year-round education is the future we must accept 
-- not fight. 
</P>
<P>
RICK A. SCOTT 
</P>
<P>
Tehachapi 
</P>
</TEXT>
