<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHANGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A lot of changes have occurred throughout the world in 1989. 
</P>
<P>
What about America? What about Los Angeles? There may be no need for a change 
in government but the problems in America are taking a back seat to those in 
the rest of the world. Change should be taking place right here. Build centers 
for the homeless. Increase the size of the Police Department. Put more money 
into the school system. Build a subway system. 
</P>
<P>
The country and this area have grown stagnant. Progress in all areas is 
necessary for the survival of this country. Is there anyone listening? Do not 
look at the television; look out the window instead. 
</P>
<P>
BRIAN RIEMER 
</P>
<P>
Malibu 
</P>
</TEXT>
