<HEADLINE>
<P>
POSTAGE INCREASES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An announcement by the postmaster general mentioned that he would seek another 
increase in the cost of first-class mail -- from 25 cents to 30 cents. 
</P>
<P>
What a hypocrisy on the general public. 
</P>
<P>
For the past several years, an average of over 95% of the mail I have received 
can be classified as "junk mail." I discussed this with my friends and 
neighbors. It seems that they, too, suffer from the deluge of junk. 
</P>
<P>
The postmaster general should treble the charges for this junk mail. It might 
afford some relief to our increasing problem with finding enough landfills for 
our waste. 
</P>
<P>
OTTO KIESSIG 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
