<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: SUPERIOR'S PROFIT UP 15% IN 4TH QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Superior Industries International Inc., a Van Nuys builder of automotive 
wheels, said it earned $5 million in the fourth quarter that ended Dec. 31, up 
15% from $4.3 million a year earlier. Revenue rose to $60.9 million from $56.7 
million, a 7% gain. 
</P>
<P>
The company said its results improved despite declining domestic auto sales 
because it increased its market for aluminum wheels and won its first contract 
with a Japanese car maker, Mazda. 
</P>
<P>
For the year that ended Dec. 31, Superior reported a 23% gain in net income to 
$16.2 million from $13.1 million in 1988. Revenues increased 23% to $246.1 
million from $200.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
Separately, Superior said it began shipments of wheels from its new 
manufacturing plant in Pittsburg, Kan. When fully operational, the plant is 
expected to employ 700 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
