<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: PERCEPTRONICS CUTS LOSSES FOR 3RD-QUARTER GAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Perceptronics Inc., a Woodland Hills maker of computer trainers and simulators 
for the military, said it earned $324,276 in the third quarter that ended Dec. 
31, compared to a loss of $2.35 million a year earlier. The company said its 
revenues decreased 22% for the quarter to $6.72 million from $8.63 million a 
year before. 
</P>
<P>
A substantial portion of net income for the quarter stemmed from a $123,100 tax 
benefit. The year-earlier results included revenues and losses from the 
company's FAAC Perceptronics unit, which it sold last spring. 
</P>
<P>
For the nine months that ended Dec. 31, Perceptronics reported a net income of 
$815,982, compared to a loss of $2.51 million in the same period a year ago. 
Nine-month revenues dropped 7% to $20.86 million from $22.49 million. 
</P>
