<TEXT>
<P>
Dov Alexander Scarf, a 38-year-old Israeli conductor, will lead the Capistrano 
Valley Symphony Sunday at 2 p.m. at the Ritz-Carlton in Dana Point, replacing 
founding music director Donn Laurence Mills, who died earlier this month. 
</P>
<P>
The program will be announced. The concert is free, but tickets are required. 
Information: (714) 240-8584. 
