<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAUNA SNOW, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
McEntire, Baby at Home: Country music star Reba McEntire, 34, and Shelby 
Stephen Blackstock, her new baby boy born over the weekend, are home from the 
hospital, McEntire's publicist said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Shelby, the first child of McEntire and her husband-manager Narvel Blackstock, 
was born Friday at 5:04 a.m. at Westside Hospital in Nashville, said Jennifer 
Bohler. He weighed 6 pounds, 10 ounces. An Oklahoma native, McEntire last June 
married Blackstock, 33, some three years after divorcing her first husband, 
Charlie Battles. SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
