<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: CANTWELL STUDENTS ACT TO KEEP RELIGIOUS 
ORDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The student body of Cantwell High School in Montebello walked out of class 
Monday to protest a decision by the Archdiocese of Los Angeles to drop the 
contract of the Congregation of Christian Brothers, a religious order that has 
run the boys' school since it opened 43 years ago. 
</P>
<P>
About 230 students left their classes and held a two-hour rally in the 
gymnasium. They asked that Archbishop Roger Mahony visit the school to witness 
the quality of education they receive from the Christian Brothers. Mahony 
announced last week that the Christian Brothers' contract would not be renewed 
and that, beginning in September, 1991, Jesuits would staff the school. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
CANTWELL HIGH SCHOOL; DEMONSTRATIONS -- LOS ANGELES COUNTY; STUDENTS; TEACHERS 
-- LOS ANGELES COUNTY; CONTRACTS; CONGREGATION OF CHRISTIAN BROTHERS; 
ARCHDIOCESE OF LOS ANGELES; CATHOLIC CHURCH -- LOS ANGELES; RELIGIOUS ORDERS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
