<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A San Diego man was in custody Monday on suspicion of murder after the stabbing 
death of another man, a San Diego police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Son Ngoc Nguyen, 35, was stabbed under his right arm during an argument late 
Saturday night in the 4300 block of Estrella Avenue, said Bill Robinson. 
</P>
<P>
Tuong Nguyen, 27, surrendered to police at 12:25 a.m. Sunday and is being held 
at County Jail, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was already dead at 11:22 p.m. Saturday when three people brought 
him to Villa View Community Hospital, a deputy coroner said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
