<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: NEW IMAGE SEEKS TO OFFER 1.1 MILLION SHARES OF STOCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New Image Industries Inc. of Canoga Park said it filed a registration statement 
with the Securities and Exchange Commission for an offering of 1.1 million 
shares of its common stock. Of the shares being offered, 1 million are being 
offered by the company, and 100,000 are being offered by shareholders. 
</P>
<P>
A company spokesman said he could not project the amount of money New Image 
will net, since the price of the stock could change before the offering becomes 
effective in late March. 
</P>
<P>
New Image's stock trades at about $12.25 a share. 
</P>
<P>
New Image markets computer systems used by hairstylists, builders, cosmetic 
surgeons and weight-loss clinics to show clients before-and-after pictures. The 
company said proceeds from the offering will be used to open regional 
headquarters in Europe, to develop new products and possibly to finance future 
acquisitions. 
</P>
