<P>
U.S., Japan Biotech Deal: IDEC Pharmaceutical Corp. of La Jolla said it entered 
a partnership believed to be the first major marketing collaboration between 
private biotech firms from the United States and Japan. An IDEC statement said 
it had entered into an agreement with the Institute of Immunology Co. of Tokyo 
that will give the institute rights in Asia to certain IDEC products plus a 
chunk of IDEC stock in exchange for market penetration for IDEC that could be 
worth up to $23 million in sales over two years. 
</P>
