<P>
30 U.S. YOUTHS HURT AS BUS LEAVES ROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A tour bus carrying American youths to a recreation center plunged from the 
road down a 130-foot embankment near the Rhine River city of Oberwesel, 
injuring 30 of the passengers, police said. Twenty of the youths were seriously 
hurt, and 10 others suffered minor injuries, a police spokesman said. He added 
that authorities had not immediately determined whether the Americans were 
tourists or relatives of military or diplomatic personnel in West Germany. 
</P>
