<P>
EAST GERMANY; 
</P>
<P>
FIRST OF THE JOBLESS REGISTER FOR BENEFITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Several thousand East Germans applied for the first benefits their government 
has ever given the unemployed, whose ranks may swell dramatically as the nation 
moves toward capitalism. 
</P>
<P>
At the moment, East Germany has a severe labor shortage because skilled workers 
continue to leave for West Germany. But industrial production has slowed, and 
the nation is threatened with financial collapse. Economists say more 
competitive Western methods will force many East German factories to close or 
lay off employees. 
</P>
