CRAZY EDDIE A NO-SHOW, FACES CONTEMPT CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEWARK, N.J. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The founder of Crazy Eddie Inc., the small electronics firm, faces criminal 
contempt charges after he again failed to appear today before a federal judge 
to answer demands he return $52 million to the United States. 
</P>
<P>
Judge Nicholas H. Politan ordered U.S. marshals to bring Eddie Antar before him 
and said a civil trial against Antar and two family members will proceed 
without the reclusive founder beginning May 1. 
