<P>
POLAND TO GET TASTE OF U.S. TV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The Wonder Years" and steamy "Santa Barbara" are among the television shows 
headed for Polish audiences under an agreement announced between Polish TV 
officials and an American outlet. 
</P>
<P>
The two-year agreement between Polish Television Channel 2 and Annapolis, Md. 
</P>
<P>
-based Conduit Internationale Films calls for provision of programming and 
selling of advertising for the station. 
</P>
<P>
Formerly one of Poland's two government-operated channels offering a slim 
variety of news, current affairs and regional programs, Channel 2 has been 
converted into a commercial operation under Poland's new, non-communist 
government. 
</P>
<P>
In a statement released with the announcement Monday, Conduit Internationale 
said it reached an agreement with the New World International production 
company to provide "The Wonder Years" for Channel 2. 
</P>
<P>
Other New World features heading for Poland include the daytime soap opera 
"Santa Barbara" and the crime-adventure show "Wise Guy." 
</P>
</TEXT>
