<P>
BLIND BOY GETTING TO BE DEEJAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HIGH POINT, N.C. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 10-year-old blind boy will get to fulfill his dream of being a disc jockey 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Joe Milam of High Point, N.C., will co-host the morning show on station WMAG 
with regular Bill Flynn, an appearance arranged after Flynn heard about how Joe 
put on a make-believe radio show at home. "I was touched by Joe's story and 
remembered how I used to pretend to do a radio show by faking it at home," 
Flynn said. "Now I just fake it at work." The station plans to let Joe run free 
by playing records, doing interviews and introducing the weather. 
</P>
</TEXT>
