<P>
BROKAW TO HOST 'NEW HOLLYWOOD' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NBC News announced Monday that Tom Brokaw will anchor a prime time documentary 
March 21 on "The New Hollywood." According to the network, the hourlong 
documentary will probe new trends in movie making, ingredients for success at 
the box office and the changing business of film production. Among those 
scheduled to be interviewed are Robert Redford, Robert De Niro, Sally Field, 
Spike Lee, Sidney Pollack and Oliver Stone. 
