<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
MARINERS SIGN GRIFFEY, 2 OTHERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEATTLE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Outfielders Ken Griffey Jr. and Jay Buhner and right-handed pitcher Dave Burba 
have agreed to one-year contracts with the Seattle Mariners, the team said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Contract terms were not announced. However, the Seattle Times reported that 
Griffey was expected to receive close to $225,000 and Buhner $175,000 base 
salary plus incentives. 
</P>
<P>
Griffey, 20, hit .261 with 16 home runs and 61 RBI in 127 games in his rookie 
season last year. He finished third in the American League's rookie of the year 
balloting. 
</P>
<P>
Griffey was paid the $68,000 minimum in 1989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
